item.description: From Stetson hats and buckskin suits to army surplus tents and Gore-Tex rain jackets, outdoor gear and its marketing in catalogs, stores, and guidebooks are a means to understanding how Americans strove for an authentic mastery of the outdoors. The argument: Consumption became central to Americansâ€™ goal of mastering the outdoors.
